title: For Sale/Trade:  Hi Point 4095 Carbine
postcontent:
As the title says I have a practically new Hi Point 4095TS carbine that I'd be interested in trading.

I just bought this last week and it is essentially new, only put 80 rounds through it. Has great sights, zero recoil and would make a great plinking/recreational gun, home defense gun, and even an interesting hunting carbine, with Kansas' recent change in hunting laws you can even hunt deer with this, power is comparable to a .41 magnum coming out of the 16in barrel. 

Say what you will about the Hi Point handguns but the carbines are almost universally well reviewed and considered to be very reliable. Will come with its box and all the factory stuff, papers, lock, tools, folding foregrip, and two ten round magazines.

I love it and hate to see it go, but I'm needing something small for summer carry, I love my Beretta 92 but its too big to carry all the time. I'm wanting to trade for a pocket sized or subcompact handgun, I have a strong preference for .40, but will consider other guns in 9mm, would also consider a .38 special snub revolver. 
I have cash that I can add for the right deal.
Dont really want to sell it, but if you arent interested in trading I will sell for $300.
